WEBVTT

00:00.149 --> 00:01.320
Previously on <i>suits:</i>

00:01.420 --> 00:03.216
We're suing you and your
entire firm for fraud.

00:03.418 --> 00:04.718
I never saw this thing
in my life.

00:04.924 --> 00:06.158
That document
never came into this office,

00:06.225 --> 00:07.359
or you would have seen it.

00:07.426 --> 00:08.426
A lot of people
are gonna think

00:08.494 --> 00:10.128
I buried that document.

00:10.196 --> 00:11.830
How can you bury
what doesn't exist?

00:11.898 --> 00:12.898
You think that I don't know
that there's a power struggle

00:12.965 --> 00:14.366
going on between Jessica
and Hardman?

00:14.433 --> 00:16.033
This guy gets one whiff
of what we've been hiding

00:16.102 --> 00:18.370
from Hardman--
I know, we can't trust him.

00:18.437 --> 00:20.972
Louis, is there anything
you want to tell me?

00:21.040 --> 00:22.674
Let me explain
something to you.

00:22.742 --> 00:24.476
That memo doesn't hurt me.
It helps me.

00:24.544 --> 00:25.944
It's gone.

00:26.012 --> 00:28.146
Your actions
have left me no choice

00:28.214 --> 00:30.182
but to terminate your employment
at Pearson Hardman,

00:30.249 --> 00:34.186
effective immediately.

00:36.000 --> 00:42.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:59.145 --> 01:02.280
Ray, I need you
to pick me up in an hour,

01:02.348 --> 01:04.916
and I need you
to bring me a tux.

01:07.053 --> 01:08.820
That's thrilling--

01:08.888 --> 01:10.388
I'm not here.

01:12.458 --> 01:13.892
God, what...

01:13.960 --> 01:15.861
what are you doing here?

01:15.928 --> 01:17.729
Are you watching
<i>Diff'rent Strokes?</i>

01:17.797 --> 01:19.798
Uh, yeah, well,
it's the touching story

01:19.866 --> 01:21.833
of a couple of orphans, so...
Don't.

01:21.901 --> 01:23.768
It's a nice building.

01:23.836 --> 01:25.370
How long ago
was it condemned?

01:25.438 --> 01:27.005
Oh, great, so did you come
all the way over here

01:27.073 --> 01:28.940
just to criticize
where I live, or...

01:29.008 --> 01:30.375
That's a side benefit.

01:30.443 --> 01:32.310
You've got to be kidding me.
What?

01:32.378 --> 01:34.045
Ah, that--
sentimental value.

01:34.113 --> 01:36.047
So just put that away.

01:36.115 --> 01:37.315
- Nice panda.
- Thank you.

01:37.383 --> 01:38.783
Grandmother.
Christmas thing.

01:38.851 --> 01:41.353
Get your tux on.
We got a situation.

01:41.420 --> 01:42.954
A situation
that requires a tux?

01:43.022 --> 01:45.023
Where--where
is this tuxedo situation?

01:45.091 --> 01:47.492
Atlantic City.
Can you get dressed now?

01:47.560 --> 01:48.593
- Yeah, I could.
- But?

01:48.661 --> 01:51.196
I don't have a tux.

01:51.264 --> 01:52.497
I'm not Bruce Wayne.

01:53.448 --> 01:55.215
Don't I know it.

02:08.496 --> 02:10.430
Wow.

02:12.667 --> 02:14.101
Rachel.

02:14.169 --> 02:15.202
Louis, hi.

02:15.270 --> 02:17.237
At the ballet.

02:17.305 --> 02:18.839
Are you an aficionado?

02:18.907 --> 02:20.607
Since I was a girl,
yes.

02:20.675 --> 02:23.110
Me too.
I mean, a boy.

02:23.178 --> 02:24.378
I got that.

02:24.445 --> 02:25.679
So are you--

02:25.747 --> 02:27.114
you here with someone?

02:27.182 --> 02:28.382
You know, Donna was supposed
to come with me,

02:28.449 --> 02:30.217
and then she cancelled
at the last minute.

02:30.285 --> 02:31.285
Oh, you talked to her?
How is she?

02:31.352 --> 02:32.486
No, I haven't.

02:32.554 --> 02:33.687
I keep calling,
but she just won't...

02:33.755 --> 02:35.122
Answer.
I know. I tried.

02:35.190 --> 02:37.324
You tried?

02:37.392 --> 02:40.127
Yeah.

02:40.195 --> 02:42.462
Are you here
with someone?

02:42.530 --> 02:43.931
Oh, I'm alone.

02:43.998 --> 02:45.632
I feel it's a better way to
experience the dance, you know?

02:45.700 --> 02:47.801
Too distracting
to have to talk about it.

02:47.869 --> 02:49.570
I just want to--
To feel it.

02:49.637 --> 02:50.671
No, I know.

02:50.738 --> 02:52.673
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

02:56.444 --> 02:57.945
I should probably
get going.

02:58.012 --> 03:01.882
Wait.
I have an extra ticket,

03:01.950 --> 03:04.117
third row.

03:04.185 --> 03:05.853
Yeah, I like to buy
a seat to my right

03:05.920 --> 03:08.989
just as a precaution.

03:09.057 --> 03:11.325
Yeah.
I would love to.

03:11.392 --> 03:13.660
- Great.
- Yeah. Okay.

03:13.728 --> 03:16.096
You just carry around
an extra tux

03:16.164 --> 03:17.297
for the random occasion?

03:17.365 --> 03:18.565
Something told me
you'd need it.

03:18.633 --> 03:20.334
And by "something,"
I mean common sense.

03:20.401 --> 03:22.636
And by "need it,"
I mean you're an idiot.

03:22.704 --> 03:24.805
Haha.
So can I ask why

03:24.873 --> 03:28.375
we are going to Atlantic City
instead of just messengering

03:28.443 --> 03:30.277
these contracts?
No.

03:30.345 --> 03:32.012
You know, I'm sensing
a little hostility,

03:32.080 --> 03:33.247
and you know what I think?

03:33.314 --> 03:35.515
I think
that you're still stung

03:35.583 --> 03:37.084
about Donna,
and you see a chance

03:37.151 --> 03:40.220
to blow off some steam,
and you need a wingman.

03:40.288 --> 03:42.656
Easy, Dr. Phil.
We're here.

03:42.724 --> 03:45.959
There.
How's that?

03:59.307 --> 04:01.508
That's right.
We're not in Kansas anymore.

04:01.576 --> 04:02.976
Let's move, Dorothy.

04:03.044 --> 04:05.245
You didn't tell me
you were bringing me here.

04:05.313 --> 04:06.980
And that's a problem how?

04:07.048 --> 04:09.316
I'm sort of banned
from here.

04:09.384 --> 04:10.817
For smoking weed?

04:10.885 --> 04:12.953
Counting cards.
I mean, I was smoking weed,

04:13.021 --> 04:14.621
but they banned me
for counting cards.

04:14.689 --> 04:16.123
What?
My brain just does it.

04:16.190 --> 04:17.724
I can't help
that it keeps track.

04:17.791 --> 04:19.226
And that's your defense?

04:19.293 --> 04:21.228
It was three years ago.
I was broke.

04:21.296 --> 04:22.963
Well, which is it,
your brain just does it,

04:23.031 --> 04:24.197
or you were broke?

04:24.265 --> 04:25.332
What are you,
some kind of lawyer?

04:25.400 --> 04:26.733
Get inside.
You're wearing a tux.

04:26.801 --> 04:29.703
They're not gonna know
who you are.

04:29.771 --> 04:32.306
Speaking of which,
this isn't Havana in the 1950s.

04:32.373 --> 04:33.640
Why do we have
to wear tuxes?

04:33.708 --> 04:34.841
What are you,
Moe Green?

04:34.909 --> 04:35.943
Moe Green lived in Vegas.

04:36.010 --> 04:37.377
I know
where Moe Green lives.

04:37.445 --> 04:39.579
Complimentary champagne?

04:39.647 --> 04:41.848
You think this happens
if you walk in here

04:41.916 --> 04:43.617
in a T-shirt
and jeans?

04:43.685 --> 04:45.185
You have a guest,
Keith Hoyt.

04:45.253 --> 04:47.187
Can you let him know
I'm here?

04:47.255 --> 04:49.589
Mr. Hoyt left a message
for you to meet him

04:49.657 --> 04:51.758
in the Poker Room,
Mr. Specter.

04:51.826 --> 04:53.226
The floor manager
assured me

04:53.294 --> 04:55.128
that he'd be kept away
from the tables.

04:55.196 --> 04:58.131
I'm sorry, I have
no record of that here, sir.

05:00.935 --> 05:02.336
Double down.

05:02.403 --> 05:03.503
Okay, so let me
get this straight,

05:03.571 --> 05:05.505
he has a gambling problem?

05:05.573 --> 05:06.974
And drinking.

05:07.041 --> 05:08.575
Why is he
in Atlantic City?

05:08.643 --> 05:10.243
Because he's
the keynote speaker

05:10.311 --> 05:11.645
at a clean energy conference,

05:11.713 --> 05:14.181
and he promised me
he'd stay out of trouble.

05:14.248 --> 05:15.749
And you took the word
of an addict?

05:18.519 --> 05:19.753
He's been clean
five years.

05:19.821 --> 05:21.321
No drinking,
no gambling.

05:21.389 --> 05:22.489
So that's why you're here.

05:22.557 --> 05:23.690
You're concerned
about him.

05:23.758 --> 05:25.359
- Yes.
- But you also want to gamble.

05:25.426 --> 05:28.061
He has a problem.
I do not have a problem.

05:28.129 --> 05:30.130
Uhhuh.

05:35.003 --> 05:37.704
Holy shit.

05:37.772 --> 05:38.905
Look at this guy.

05:38.973 --> 05:41.008
Those are $25,000 chips.

05:41.075 --> 05:44.644
That's three stacks of four...
by seven...

05:44.712 --> 05:47.147
That is $3,125,000.

05:47.215 --> 05:49.683
That's Keith.

05:49.751 --> 05:52.819
Well, at least we don't have
to worry about him losing.

05:52.887 --> 05:55.288
All in.

05:55.356 --> 05:56.823
- Or...
- Keith.

05:56.891 --> 05:58.892
Harvey.

05:58.960 --> 06:00.394
This is a bad idea.

06:00.461 --> 06:02.496
You haven't seen my hand.

06:05.800 --> 06:08.535
I call.

06:16.244 --> 06:17.611
Straight.

06:23.351 --> 06:24.851
Full house.

06:24.919 --> 06:26.286
- He's got one out.
- Yeah, we're fine

06:26.354 --> 06:29.656
- unless the river's a...
- 10 of clubs.

06:40.668 --> 06:43.036
That is some tough luck
right there.

06:43.104 --> 06:46.006
Tommy, please,
just give me 48 hours.

06:46.074 --> 06:48.742
Sorry, Keith.
Deal's a deal.

06:48.810 --> 06:50.744
- Tommy.
- That was insane.

06:50.812 --> 06:52.946
You just lost $3 million.
Who the hell's that guy?

06:53.014 --> 06:56.516
It's worse.
That napkin--

06:56.584 --> 06:58.518
Harvey, I just
lost my company.

